President Donald Trump and Prime Minister Boris Johnson met at the G7 Summit in France and reaffirmed the Special Relationship between the United States and the United Kingdom. They discussed the depth of their security and defense partnership and committed to increasing cooperation. They also discussed the opportunities presented by the UK leaving the European Union, including a comprehensive trade agreement. The leaders emphasized the importance of free, fair, and reciprocal trade and discussed the role of investment in their respective economies. They directed officials to launch a "Special Relationship Economic Working Group" to develop market-oriented principles for economic growth and increase bilateral cooperation.